error<T>(msg : String) : T

getEqualFor<T>(t : T) : EqualFunction<T>

Returns an EqualFunction (T -> T -> Bool). It works for any type. Custom Classes must provide an "equals(other : T) : Bool" method or a "compare(other : T) : Int" method otherwise an exception will be thrown.

getEqualForType<T>(v : ValueType) : EqualFunction<T>

getHashFor<T>(t : T) : HashFunction<T>

getHashForType<T>(v : ValueType) : HashFunction<T>

getOrderFor<T>(t : T) : OrderFunction<T>

Returns a OrderFunction (T -> T -> Int). It works for any type expect TFunction. Custom Classes must provide a compare(other : T) : Int method or an exception will be thrown.

getOrderForType<T>(v : ValueType) : OrderFunction<T>

getShowFor<T>(t : T) : ShowFunction<T>

Returns a ShowFunction (T -> String). It works for any type. For Custom Classes you must provide a toString() method, otherwise the full class name is returned.

getShowForType<T>(v : ValueType) : ShowFunction<T>
